content.content: 1. (1) In this section, “elevating device” has the same meaning as in subsection 1 (1) of Ontario Regulation 209/01 (Elevating Devices) made under the Act. (2) The provisions of this Regulation that are set out in the Schedule, as they apply to the classes of elevating devices set out in paragraphs 1, 2, 4.1, 5, 6, 7, 9, 10, 11, 12 and 13 of subsection 1 (5) of Ontario Regulation 209/01 (Elevating Devices) made under the Act, are prescribed for the purposes of clause 32.1 (1) (a) of the Act. (3) The amount of an administrative penalty that an assessor may, by order, impose under 32.1 (1) of the Act against a person for each contravention of a provision of Ontario Regulation 209/01 (Elevating Devices) made under the Act that is set out in the Schedule to this Regulation is as follows: 1. If the person on whom the penalty is imposed is a contractor, $5,000. 2. If the person on whom the penalty is imposed is a licence holder for an elevating device or an owner, $3,000. 3. If the person on whom the penalty is imposed is any other person, $1,000.
content.raw_html:
1. (1) In this section,

“elevating device” has the same meaning as in subsection 1 (1) of Ontario Regulation 209/01 (Elevating Devices) made under the Act.

(2) The provisions of this Regulation that are set out in the Schedule, as they apply to the classes of elevating devices set out in paragraphs 1, 2, 4.1, 5, 6, 7, 9, 10, 11, 12 and 13 of subsection 1 (5) of Ontario Regulation 209/01 (Elevating Devices) made under the Act, are prescribed for the purposes of clause 32.1 (1) (a) of the Act.

(3) The amount of an administrative penalty that an assessor may, by order, impose under 32.1 (1) of the Act against a person for each contravention of a provision of Ontario Regulation 209/01 (Elevating Devices) made under the Act that is set out in the Schedule to this Regulation is as follows:

1. If the person on whom the penalty is imposed is a contractor, $5,000.

2. If the person on whom the penalty is imposed is a licence holder for an elevating device or an owner, $3,000.

3. If the person on whom the penalty is imposed is any other person, $1,000.

content.content: 2. An order made under subsection 32.1 (1) of the Act is deemed to have been served, (a) on the day it is given, if it is given by personal service; (b) on the day it is sent by email, if it is sent by email; or (c) on the third day after it is mailed, if it is sent by registered mail.
content.raw_html:
2. An order made under subsection 32.1 (1) of the Act is deemed to have been served,

(a) on the day it is given, if it is given by personal service;

(b) on the day it is sent by email, if it is sent by email; or

(c) on the third day after it is mailed, if it is sent by registered mail.

content.content: 3. An order imposing an administrative penalty against a person shall specify that the person is required to pay the penalty within 30 days of being served with the order imposing the penalty.
content.raw_html: 3. An order imposing an administrative penalty against a person shall specify that the person is required to pay the penalty within 30 days of being served with the order imposing the penalty.
